<li><strong>Dumbbell Curl — </strong>2 sets x 10–12 repetitions.</li>



<li><strong>EZ Bar Preacher Curl — </strong>3 sets x 8–10 repetitions (drop set).</li>



<li><strong>Cable Cross Body Triceps Push — </strong>2 sets x 10–15 repetitions.</li>



<li><strong>Low Pulley Cable Curl With V-Bar — </strong>2 sets x 10–12 repetitions.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Diet and Nutrition</h2>



<p>Chris prides himself on a high-quality diet during the off-season and prep. His autoimmune disease means that he focuses on high-quality, nutritious foods spread evenly throughout the day.&nbsp;</p>



<p>These are examples of what some of his days look like based on his well-documented social media videos.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Off-season Diet</h3>



<p>His calories tend to hover around 4500–5000 in the off-season. During this, he focuses on eating six small meals consisting of lots of protein, high-quality carbohydrates, and healthy fats. Throughout the day, he also takes some of his <em>CBum</em> supplements.</p>



