<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Competition Diet</h3>



<p>As he approaches pre-season, he tends to taper his calories down to 3000–4000 per day. Before a competition, his calories may get as low as 2500–2700.</p>



<p>During this, he cuts out some of the extra oils, sauces, and small treats. His principal focus is on high-quality protein and carbohydrates that he can use to fuel his training. He tends to use carb cycling throughout his competition diet, pairing his high-volume training days with his high-carb days.</p>



<p>This is an example of his typical daily intake. Again, his transparent social media presence means he documents this for everyone to see.</p>



